Title: Avoid duplicate git queries between housekeeping and healthcheck sub-skill
Status: open
Created: 2026-04-27
Author: claude

--- log ---
2026-04-27T00:00Z claude created

--- body ---
## Problem

Housekeeping calls `healthcheck` as a Skill tool (same session). The healthcheck
skill re-runs all git queries (fetch, branch list, worktree list, PR list) that
housekeeping already ran in earlier turns. This duplicates 5–8 Bash calls and
re-populates the LLM context with redundant output.

## Solution

Option A: Inline healthcheck logic into housekeeping — remove the sub-skill call,
fold the checks directly. Simpler, one session, no duplication.

Option B: Run healthcheck FIRST and pass its output as structured context to the
housekeeping agent, so housekeeping doesn't re-query.

Option A is simpler and preferred given the skill runs in the same session anyway.

## Acceptance criteria

- No duplicate git queries across housekeeping + healthcheck in a single run
- Healthcheck report still generated and committed
- Turn count for housekeeping reduced by ~5–8 turns
